I took MGT223 with Losell as well and I've got to say I've learned everything except for management accounting.  There isn't much to learn in management accounting, to be frank, and what Losell tries to do is incorporate actually useful skills such as team work, critical thinking and presenting into her classes. It's more about overall management.

HEYYY What's all this Losell-bashing going on in here? She's actually a very nice person, and really does WANT to help her students!
